Afrobeat sensation, Icezy is set to make his 2022 music debut with an alluring Afrobeat single titled ‘Body Riddim’. ‘Body Riddim’ is a blend of modern Afrobeat rhythm and soothing eulogies. Born Isaac Akanno, the Imo State native is a singer/songwriter who is passionate about music and promoting the rich African rhythm through creative sounds and inspiring messaging. ‘Body Riddim’ is Icezy’s first official single after signing on to a new record label, Pixy Entertainment.   Veteran highlife singer Orlando Julius dies     Gulder Ultimate Search 12 winner Odudu returns to Uyo     The Real Housewives Of Lagos stars break record after first…   He recently went viral online for his recent cover of the popular Afrobeat single, ‘Finesse’ by Pheelz featuring BNXN, demonstrating his vocal prowess and musical versatility and creativity. ‘Body Riddim’ which is set for release on May 13th 2022, embodies a flow that leaves you no choice but to move your body to the rhythm that reflects the energy and high spirit of Icezy. The lyrics combine raw everyday Nigerian Pidgin English with subtle metaphors that descriptively tell how he is madly in love with the body of a sexy lady, adding originality and a distinct flow and sound to the beat. Produced by Intellectual Proparty, ‘Body Riddim’ was inspired by the voluptuous look and appeal of Kenyan lawyer and content creator, Corazon Kwamboka who happens to be Icezy’s celebrity crush.